==Old English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'bera/
===Etymology===
From West Germanic ''*beran-'', from Indo-European ''*bher-'' ‘brown animal’.  Cognate with Old High German ''[[bero]]'' (German ''[[Bär]]''), Middle Dutch ''bere'' (Dutch ''[[beer]]''), Old Norse ''ber-'' ‘bears’ (used in compounds).  A North Germanic variant, ''*bernu-'', gave Old Norse {{Latinx|[[bjǫrn]]}} (Swedish ''[[björn]]'').  The IE root is also the source of Common Slavic ''*bьrlogъ'' (Russian [[берлога]] ‘den’, compare ''[[brloga]]'').
===Noun===
'''bera''' ''m'' (pl. ''beran'')

# [[bear]]

